                   and also a Book of the Canons of the Church of Ireland? (Canon 47.)

9. Doth your Minister declare to the People every Sunday at the time appointed in the Communion-Service,
                  Rubr. Commun. the several Holy days and Fasting-days in the Week following; and doth he observe them? (Canon 7.) Doth he also read all the Canons publickly in the Church Once every Year;

                     King's Declaration. Anno 10. & 11. Car. 1. c. 1. Anno 14 & 15. Car. 2. c. 1. &c. 23. and the Act against Swearing; and that for keeping the 29th of May and the 23d of October a Thanksgiving.
